The paper focuses on designing a data transformation paradigm that facilitates verification for end-users in a Programming By Example (PBE) system. This involves clustering patterns in input and output data to allow for pattern-level verification, and generating transformation programs as regular-expression replace operations. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HCI) sub-category, as it deals with improving the usability of PBE systems for end-users. It also involves working with data, which suggests that it could belong to the Databases (cs.DB) or Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach to data transformation, which could fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves experimental comparisons with existing data transformation tools, which suggests that it could also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
